prompt: Name one type of tree fruit. Answer concisely in one paragraph.
output: Apple is a type of tree fruit that is widely grown and consumed around the world. Apples are a member of the rose family (Rosaceae) and belong to the genus Malus. They come in various shapes, sizes, and colors, including red, green, yellow, and even black. Apples are known for their sweet or tart flavor and are often used in cooking, baking, and as a snack. They are also rich in vitamins and minerals such as vitamin C, fiber, and potassium. Apple trees typically bear fruit after three to five years of planting and can produce up to several hundred apples per year depending on the variety and growing conditions. Apple trees have been cultivated for thousands of years and are an important part of many cultures
